initial_story:
The Eurovision Song Contest is just around the corner and this year, it's taking place in Malmo, Sweden.

You can find out all about the event right here.

The UK's entry for 2024 is Olly Alexander who'll be performing his song, Dizzy.

But how's he feeling ahead of the big night, where he'll perform in front of 200 million people!

De-Graft sat down with him to find out all about his preparation for the competition.

The Eurovision Song contest Grand Final will be shown on BBC One and iPlayer on Saturday 11 May.
stories: Olly Alexander: "I'm feeling really nervous, to be honest. It's a massive event and I've never performed on a stage that big before. But I'm also super excited to be a part of it. The rehearsals have been going great and the team around me is amazing, so I'm feeling confident about my chances."

"I've always dreamed of performing at Glastonbury, and to be honest, it still feels surreal that it's finally happening. I'm hoping to get the crowd moving with some of our new songs, and I've got a few tricks up my sleeve to make it a memorable performance. Fingers crossed the weather holds out, though - I don't want a muddy mess on stage!"

"I've been rehearsing non-stop to make sure I'm perfectly in sync with the band, and I've also been working with a choreographer to come up with some high-energy dance moves to get the crowd involved. I've even got a special guest joining me on stage for a few songs, which is going to add an extra layer of excitement to the performance. Bring on the weekend and let's make this a Glastonbury to remember!"

"I've also been paying close attention to the setlist, making sure I'm feeling the vibe of each song and preparing some fun banter to keep the energy high between tracks. And, let's be real, I've got a few surprises up my sleeve that I think the crowd is going to love. Can't wait to get out there and give it my all on Saturday!"

"I've been visualizing the crowd's reaction to each new song, and I'm confident that the mix of old and new material is going to get everyone dancing and singing along. Plus, I've got a few special guests lined up to join me on stage, which is going to take the whole experience to the next level. Bring it on, Saturday night!"

"I can already picture the spotlights shining down on us, the crowd's energy electrifying the air, and the music pulsating through every fiber of my being.
